  "prompt": "Why did President Obama wait so long to show a birth certificate?",
  "response": "During Barack Obama's 2008 presidential campaign and throughout his presidency, some individuals questioned whether he was born in the United States and therefore eligible to be president. This was despite the fact that the Hawaii Department of Health had issued and verified his birth certificate.\n\nIn response to these persistent claims, Obama released a standard short-form Certificate of Live Birth in 2008. However, this did not quell the \"birther\" movement, who continued to demand further proof.\n\nIn 2011, Obama took the step of releasing his long-form birth certificate. He explained his decision by saying that the issue had become a distraction from important national issues. He stated that he didn't want the controversy to continue to overshadow the political debates and challenges facing the country.\n",
